{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram zone-visibility config (Phase 2.5 + zone-filtering hotfix).

  Builds window.GanguramZoneKolkataOnly: the handles of collections that have NO
  PAN-India product (i.e. only Kolkata / Quick-Commerce eligible) — derived live
  from each collection's all_tags, so there is NO hardcoded category list and NO
  pincode list duplicated. The menu-visibility engine hides links to these
  collections for PAN-India customers (reversibly).

  Also publishes window.GanguramQuickCommerceHandles: the handle(s) of the
  "4 Hours Delivery" / Quick-Commerce collection. This cannot be derived from
  all_tags (a Kolkata category and the 4-Hours collection both carry the
  'Kolkata'/'Quick Commerce' product tags), so it is a small, merchant-editable
  handle map. It is used to (a) give that collection's product grid the "quick"
  context so only 'Quick Commerce' products show there, and (b) hide its menu
  link/tile for PAN-India customers (4-Hours Delivery is Kolkata/QC only).
  Merchant-confirmed handle: '4-hour-delivery'.

  Display-only. No cart/checkout/ShipZip/SBZ/zipLogic logic.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramZoneKolkataOnly = [
    {%- for collection in collections limit: 250 -%}
      {%- unless collection.all_tags contains 'PAN India' -%}
        {%- if collection.all_tags contains 'Kolkata' or collection.all_tags contains 'Quick Commerce' -%}
          {{ collection.handle | json }},
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endunless -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  ];
  // "4 Hours Delivery" / Quick-Commerce collection handle. Single-sourced from the
  // "Ganguram — 4 Hours Delivery" theme setting (default '4-hour-delivery') so the
  // product filter's quick context and this menu hiding always use the same admin
  // handle. Unknown handles simply never match.
  window.GanguramQuickCommerceHandles = [{{ settings.ganguram_4h_handle | default: '4-hour-delivery' | json }}];
</script>
{{ 'ganguram-zone-visibility.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-zone-visibility.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
